# ⚙️ DataForge

A web app that lets anyone upload a CSV, Excel, or JSON file and clean, explore, and export it — no code required.

**Live demo:** _add your Streamlit Cloud link here after deploying_

## Features

- **Light/dark mode toggle**, green accent branding
- **Try with example data** — built-in movies dataset (with missing values & a duplicate row) so visitors can test it instantly without their own file
- **50 MB upload limit** to keep things stable on free hosting
- **Upload** any CSV, Excel (.xlsx), or JSON file
- **Clean**
  - Identify missing values (count + % per column)
  - Fill missing values (mean, median, mode, custom value, forward/backward fill) or drop rows
  - Detect and remove duplicate rows (full row or by chosen columns)
  - Convert column data types (string, integer, float, datetime, category, boolean)
- **Filter & Sort**
  - Dynamic filters built per column (range sliders for numbers, date pickers for dates, multiselect/search for text)
  - Multi-column sorting
  - Promote a filtered/sorted view to your working dataset, or download it directly
- **Visualize**
  - Histograms, bar charts, scatter plots, box plots, line charts, pie charts, correlation heatmaps
- **Statistics**
  - Numeric summary stats (`describe()`)
  - Categorical value counts and percentages
- **Export**
  - Download the cleaned dataset as CSV, Excel, or JSON

## Tech stack

- [Streamlit](https://streamlit.io/) — UI and app framework
- [Pandas](https://pandas.pydata.org/) — data manipulation
- [Plotly](https://plotly.com/python/) — interactive charts
- [OpenPyXL](https://openpyxl.readthedocs.io/) — Excel read/write

## Run locally

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
streamlit run app.py
```

## Deploy

Push to GitHub, then deploy for free on [Streamlit Community Cloud](https://streamlit.io/cloud) by pointing it at `app.py` in this repo.

## Privacy

Uploaded files are processed only in-memory for your session and are not stored.
